review_text: We had an incredible stay at Posada Eva. The host Valentina did a great job making sure we were comfortable and enjoyed our stay in Los Roques. place_address: Frente a la Laguna, La Laguna 118, Gran Roque 1161, Dependencias Federales Venezolanas, Venezuela
review_text:
We recently had the pleasure of staying at Posada Eva in Los Roques, and it was nothing short of incredible! From the moment we arrived, we were greeted by the most professional and friendly staff who made us feel right at home ( Yuli, Mercedes, Joha, Mafer, Barbie, Pedro and Israel )  They went above and beyond to provide us with all the information we needed to fully enjoy and explore the stunning cays of Los Roques. ( Thanks Juan, Jose, Wilberg )

The food at Posada Eva was a culinary delight! ( Gustavo, Jenny, Mary and Jesus ) Every day, we were treated to different, delicious meals that were full of flavor and beautifully presented, the breakfast was delicious, the lunch and the dinner a tasteful and lovely surprise every single time we were sitting at the table.

The entire team at Posada Eva was exceptional, especially the sailors who took us to different cays each day. They were always punctual, setting up our beach camp with care and picking us up with a smile. Their warmth and professionalism at telling us about Los Roques and showing us incredible snorkelling spots ( Thanks Wilberg and Jose for incredible snorkeling at Cayo de los Bobos and Thanks Juan for all those trips full of information )  made our daily excursions even more enjoyable.

We were also impressed by the cleanliness of the rooms. Every corner of Posada Eva was spotless, and the attention to detail in maintaining such high standards was truly commendable. The location of Posada Eva, along with El Recuerdo, was perfect close to everything and offering a cool, relax vibe.

What made our stay even more special was how at home we felt. The warm and welcoming environment made it easy to connect with the staff and other guests. We left with new friends and unforgettable memories.

We can't recommend Posada Eva enough! If you're planning to visit Los Roques, this is the place to stay. We will definitely be back in the future to continue exploring this beautiful paradise. Our experience was truly exceptional, and we highly recommend it to anyone looking for an unforgettable holidays!!!

review_text:
Absolute perfection in Gran Roque!
Posada Galapagos is a real gem. I wish my three nights stay could have lasted much longer!

The best part is the restaurant which serves 5* meals, based on fresh and local products.

I normally like to add a constructively critical comment to my reviews but there is not a single moment at La Posada Galapagos that wasn't amazing.
Muchas gracias querida Paola (y a tu equipo) por todo!

review_text: Le ragazze che curano la posada e preparano la  colazione sono disponibili e gentilissime e le stanze sono davvero pulite. Tutte le altre strutture dell'isola, che purtroppo non abbiamo trovato in booking al momento della prenotazione, offrono un rapporto qualit√†/prezzo nettamente migliore con pacchetti di colazione, pranzo,merenda e cena (tuto rigorosamente preparato con pesce fresco). Abbiamo ovviamente chiesto inizialmente qualche cena in posada, alla cui richiesta ci √® stato detto si la sera e no di nuovo la mattina per tre giorni di fila, costringendoci a improvvisare (incappando in trappole per turisti da 140 euro per due per una cena di poche e piccole portate). Il wi-fi, inserito tra i servizi, non esiste in posada, tanto che dovevamo attendere la cena nell'altra posada per collegarci. Alla Y papaya hanno solamente hotspot dal cellulare di Africa (che viene acceso se lei √® presente, su richiesta esplicita e spesso tolto quasi subito,  costringendo l'ospite a chiedere costantemente la linea). La linea ci √® stata data la prima volta dopo varie insistenze passati gi√† 3 giorni (sembrava non avere tempo ogniqualvolta lo chiedevamo). La cava, che viene consegnata vuota  costringendo l'ospite a reperire ghiaccio, cibo e acqua, √® in realt√† servizio incluso in altre posade (come guaripete e anche le altre dell"isola) che porta la cava piena di ghiaccio, acqua, tris di cibi (in genere pesce fresco  cucinato), frutta biscotti e patatine direttamente sulla barca delle escursioni. In generale, il servizio e (nel nostro caso) neanche la gentilezza e disponibilit√† valgono i costi di pernotto. Tutte le altre posade che abbiamo conosciuto e alle quali ci siamo appoggiate (bellissime e cordiali) sono state ben pi√π accoglienti. Nonostante la gentilezza che abbiamo sempre riservato alla propriet√† non possiamo dire di aver trovato sempre cordialit√† e disponibilit√† da Africa ( ci √® stata negata anche una bottiglia di acqua che avevamo dimenticato di prendere per la notte, dal momento che era tutto gi√† chiuso, dicendoci che la bottiglia era intatta). Abbiamo poi capito dalla conversazione con africa, che ci ha riferito esplicitamente che fino a 10 anni prima aveva molti italiani in posada che non vedeva l'ora andassero via perch√© non li sopportava, la ragione della poca cordialit√† nei nostri confronti rispetto agli altri ospiti (comunque conversazione che non ti fa sentire a "casa"). Consigliamo  vivamente, specie ai nostri connazionali di scegliere soluzioni diverse. Ivano e la moglie di galapagos, Tiziana e Jos√© di guaripeye (la migliore!) , acquamarina e i simpaticissimi proprietari di mediterraneo, Maria di Los Kankises sono tutti fantastici . Insomma, √® un viaggio fantastico che vale la pena fare e per il quale vale la pena investire non poco, ma tornassi indietro di certo prediligerei il lavoro e la professionalit√† di altre strutture!

review_text:

I can't find enough words to express our gratitude to the entire team, especially Carlos, the manager, Bony, Gian, Karelys, and Wiston. Their attention to detail and warmth made us feel incredibly welcome and right at home.

My son is a fussy eater, but Karelys and the team went above and beyond, cooking exactly what he wanted, which we really appreciated.

We loved Los Roques so much that after one week, we decided to return and stay at Casa de Sol again for longer 5 days. This time, Barbara assisted us with our accommodation at Casa de Sol and flight, and I can't thank her enough for everything she did for us. She went above and beyond to ensure we had everything we needed, and the communication and service were flawless.

The team at the posada is truly amazing, and I can't recommend them enough. Thank you for making our stay so memorable. We‚Äôll definitely see you next time!

review_text:
A Glorious Stay at Posada La Corsaria: A Hidden Gem in Los Roques

Our recent visit to Posada La Corsaria in the stunning Los Roques archipelago was nothing short of magical. As a group of 12 adults and 2 children hailing from Portugal, we were warmly welcomed into this cozy haven, where every detail was crafted to ensure a remarkable experience.

From the moment we arrived, it was clear that Posada La Corsaria is defined by its warmth and hospitality. The staff members were incredibly kind and dedicated, going above and beyond to cater to our every need. Their genuine smiles and willingness to help made us feel right at home. The accommodations were exceptional, equipped with air conditioning and comfortable beds that provided the perfect sanctuary after a day of exploration.

The culinary experience at the posada was simply outstanding. Each meal was a delightful journey through local flavors, showcasing the region's freshest ingredients. The children particularly enjoyed the variety of options, and we, as adults, savored every bite of the beautifully presented dishes.

Moreover, the posada's partnerships with local fishermen and boat operators enriched our stay immeasurably. These collaborations allowed us to explore the pristine waters and secret beaches of Los Roques, guided by knowledgeable locals who shared their passion for their homeland. Their insights made our adventures even more enjoyable and unforgettable.

Safety is a paramount concern for any traveler, and we were pleased to find that Los Roques offers a level of security comparable to many European destinations. The tranquility of the island allowed us to explore with peace of mind, giving us more time to appreciate its breathtaking beauty. The turquoise waters, white sandy beaches, and vibrant marine life created a picture-perfect backdrop for relaxation and adventure.

In sum, our stay at Posada La Corsaria was a true delight from start to finish. We wholeheartedly encourage all Europeans to consider visiting this beautiful archipelago. Discovering the charm of Los Roques, experiencing the warmth of its people, and enjoying the exclusive comfort of Posada La Corsaria will surely create memories to last a lifetime. Do not miss out on the chance to experience this hidden gem ‚Äì it is a paradise waiting to be explored!

place_address: Calle Bolivar Gran Roque, Gran Roque 1161, Dependencias Federales Venezolanas, Venezuela
review_text: I honestly believe there are not enough words to describe how wonderful this place is. My wife and I stayed here for a short getaway of three days and our experience was far above what we considered fantastic before. These people have raised the bar very, very high. This posada is a lovely place.  We stayed in a beautiful two storey bedroom that was beautiful. We were amazed by the level of attention to details and the beautiful and well looked after decoration.  But the icing of the cake was the service provided by its employees.  We cannot appraise enough how courteous, focused on us and approachable were the staff. We cannot finish this review by recognizing them  by names. Jonathan was just formidable. The cook Ana was amazing. She was on top of all our dietary requirements. I was on a special diet for medical reasons and she went over and above,  definitely walked the extra mile to ensure that my meals were according to my requirements.  Giovanni was also a very nice guy, always ensuring that our luggage was safe. Just a tip: don't waste your time trying to hire a boat from the locals in town. This Posada has it's own boat and the price is quite similar,  so it is well worth paying the extra quid but the comfort is definitely superior.  No doubt we will come back some time,  hopefully soon

Towels and sheets weren‚Äôt changed, a clump of (someone else‚Äôs hair in the shower), a pile of wet towels in the shower after a day, and there‚Äôs barely any light (feels a bit like a prison). In fact most of the rooms seem like they don‚Äôt have windows at all . The rooms and furniture are extremely outdated.  Just a couple of rooms with balconies which look nice. We left the premises early and felt it was worth losing the money. Honestly the food was okay. We moved to posada Chelonia. Gorgeous and not considerably more considering the value. For quality and cleanliness we suggest Caracol and Acaurela. I hate leaving a negative review but there are much better posadas. I‚Äôve never left a hotel before having paid in advance.

place_address: Calle Bolivar Gran Roque, Gran Roque 1161, Dependencias Federales Venezolanas, Venezuela
review_text:
Actually a very nice place. The food was the best (taste and presentation) I had in Venezuela. The chef certainly knows his job. The staff had been very helpful and friendly.
Why only 2 stars? We payed around USD 130 (payed in BsF). And this was per Person! For this price you would expect so much more. More attention, bigger room, more cleaning, more included services, more of everything.

place_address: Calle Bolivar Gran Roque, Gran Roque 1161, Dependencias Federales Venezolanas, Venezuela
review_text: I honestly believe there are not enough words to describe how wonderful this place is. My wife and I stayed here for a short getaway of three days and our experience was far above what we considered fantastic before. These people have raised the bar very, very high. This posada is a lovely place.  We stayed in a beautiful two storey bedroom that was beautiful. We were amazed by the level of attention to details and the beautiful and well looked after decoration.  But the icing of the cake was the service provided by its employees.  We cannot appraise enough how courteous, focused on us and approachable were the staff. We cannot finish this review by recognizing them  by names. Jonathan was just formidable. The cook Ana was amazing. She was on top of all our dietary requirements. I was on a special diet for medical reasons and she went over and above,  definitely walked the extra mile to ensure that my meals were according to my requirements.  Giovanni was also a very nice guy, always ensuring that our luggage was safe. Just a tip: don't waste your time trying to hire a boat from the locals in town. This Posada has it's own boat and the price is quite similar,  so it is well worth paying the extra quid but the comfort is definitely superior.  No doubt we will come back some time,  hopefully soon

place_address: Calle Bolivar Gran Roque, Gran Roque 1161, Dependencias Federales Venezolanas, Venezuela
review_text: I honestly believe there are not enough words to describe how wonderful this place is. My wife and I stayed here for a short getaway of three days and our experience was far above what we considered fantastic before. These people have raised the bar very, very high. This posada is a lovely place.  We stayed in a beautiful two storey bedroom that was beautiful. We were amazed by the level of attention to details and the beautiful and well looked after decoration.  But the icing of the cake was the service provided by its employees.  We cannot appraise enough how courteous, focused on us and approachable were the staff. We cannot finish this review by recognizing them  by names. Jonathan was just formidable. The cook Ana was amazing. She was on top of all our dietary requirements. I was on a special diet for medical reasons and she went over and above,  definitely walked the extra mile to ensure that my meals were according to my requirements.  Giovanni was also a very nice guy, always ensuring that our luggage was safe. Just a tip: don't waste your time trying to hire a boat from the locals in town. This Posada has it's own boat and the price is quite similar,  so it is well worth paying the extra quid but the comfort is definitely superior.  No doubt we will come back some time,  hopefully soon

place_address: Archipielago Los Roques Gran Roque, Gran Roque 1116, Dependencias Federales Venezolanas, Venezuela
review_text:
Cannot recommend this place enough!

The owner and staff are so friendly (they felt like a family away from home). I actually had a hard time leaving (not just because of the pretty beaches and water).

The food was different every single day (you have quite a few choices for breakfast, you get a lunch box for the beach and dinners were 4 courses, main was the catch of the day), plentiful and gorgeous (I bow to the cooks) and everyone was so attentive when it came to delivering the best possible experience (I'm just sorry that my Spanish was worse than basic and I couldn't have a proper talk with them). Full board is the way to go. They also offer a wide range of drinks (to drink in or to take to the beach with you).

They have quite a few rooms (different sizes), but I'm sure any is great (you have AC, TV, comfy beds, books,...). We were well satisfied with ours. They kept it clean every single day and always took great care in case we needed anything else.

There were a few islands included in our boarding and we also chose some that weren't and the staff took care of everything. They even booked our return tickets from Caracas to Los Roques and arranged a guide on mainland to accompany us from Caracas airport to the hotel and back.

If you are looking for a total relaxation with great food and family-like atmosphere, this is *the place to stay* for sure. You won't be sorry.

They have quite a few rooms (different sizes), but I'm sure any is great (you have AC, TV, comfy beds, books,...). We were well satisfied with ours. They kept it clean every single day and always took great care in case we needed anything else.

There were a few islands included in our boarding and we also chose some that weren't and the staff took care of everything. They even booked our return tickets from Caracas to Los Roques and arranged a guide on mainland to accompany us from Caracas airport to the hotel and back.

If you are looking for a total relaxation with great food and family-like atmosphere, this is *the place to stay* for sure. You won't be sorry.

review_text: It's my first time in Los Roques and I felt that the customer service at this place was really bad. I am so disappointed. I invited someone from Germany to Venezuela and the front man in a white t-shirt, a young person, was so unfriendly and rude and told me they didn't have toilet service after he saw someone coming out of the toilet üöª he did lied to me and I was shocked at the way he talked to me. However, I went to grab some cocktails and some food and the young girl with glasses in a white t-shirt behind the bar told me that they don't have a card payment connection service. For all I know this could happen and I kindly asked them to let me know as soon as they have access to the payment connection service. A few minutes after my request, another person paid with card, and I üòÆ I kept asking them, they lied to me again. I have never experienced such poor service except for a smiling person with a brown t-shirt and a very nice man renting out paddleboards. He was as nice and friendly as people should be to Let them feel welcome in Venezuela. I hope you don't have this bad service, it really wasn't nice.

place_address: W8XC+7MG, Gran Roque 1161, Dependencias Federales Venezolanas, Venezuela
review_text:
Ha sido un experiencia nefasta. Hay gatos sin desparasitar por toda la posada; se meten hasta por las habitaciones de los hu√©spedes. Una de las gatas esta enferma y campa a sus anchas por los espacios comunes, por la cocina, por encima de las mesas donde luego se posa comida o se come‚Ä¶
Las cucarachas salen de los desagues de las duchas cuando se usan. Hemos encontrado en la habitacion y tambien en las zonas comunes.
Hay mosquitos por toda la posada, muchisimos. A pesar de que hay mosquiteras (con un monton de agujeros) en las camas, cuando sales a desayunar, te comen los pies y las piernas
Pocos enchufes en las habitaciones y algunos de los que hay no funcionan.
EL aire acondicionado hace el mismo ruido que una aspiradora
En la posada no hay agua caliente; y apenas sale tampoco agua aunque sea fria, de las duchas.
Tambi√©n estuvimos un dia entero sin agua para rellenar las pocetas (wcs).
Y un dia entero sin luz.
Las ventanas no cierran bien y por la noche entran a la habitacion todo tipo de bichos (mosquitos, cucarachas, gusanos, lagartijas‚Ä¶ y una noche hasta un gato)
A pesar de lo que ponga en la pagina web, en esta posada NO hay wifi.
Nunca fueron puntuales en los desayunos, lunchs y cenas.

Por parte de la due√±a, trato desagradable durante la reserva. Y durante nuestra estancia, la propietaria estaba ebria y colocada.

place_address: W8XC+7MG, Gran Roque 1161, Federal Dependencies of Venezuela, Venezuela
review_text:
A very nice place to stay in Grand Roque, only 10 min walk from the airport. Everyone was super nice and helpful. The room was cleaned regularly. We had B&B. The breakfast was good as well (i.e: fresh fruits, fresh juice, pancakes, omelette).
The rooms have garden-bathrooms, which we loved!
The price/quality is great compared to other posadas on the island.
They offer free wifi, but if you need good internet connection, get a Venezuelan e-sim card, because the internet is poor on the entire island.

place_address: W8XC+7MG, Gran Roque 1161, Federal Dependencies of Venezuela, Venezuela
review_text:
100% satisfied with the posada.

Breakfast was always fresh. always had fruits and fresh juice also pankakes, eggs and/or other food.

The room was clean and it had nets above bed to protect from mosquitoes. There is also fans to cool down during the night wich is very nice. The toilet and ahower is outside with a small garden where you can dry clothes if you want.

The staff is very friendly. They are always happy to help e.g. if you need something for cooking. They also always have cold drinkable water in the fridge for free.

The posada is located right at the beach with an awesome view to the water.

At the end they offered free luggage transportation to airport.

The price is affordable and you get very good value for the money.

review_text:
We stayed 2 weeks in Los Roques.

This ended up beeing our favorite restaurant.

Everything is fresh. I especially liked the Tataki Bora and the Fosforera.

But really everything on the menu is great.

Price is reasonable, you can have a good dinner for under 35$.

Service is very friendly.

Also one of the few restaurants with view to the water and boats. You can watch birds flying and/or haunting on the shore.

Also good place for the sunset

place_address: Los Roques, Plaza Bol√≠var, Posada El Recuerdo, Gran Roque 1161, Dependencias Federales Venezolanas, Venezuela
review_text:
Las cenas muy escasas, en el primer desayuno las panquecas crudas, sin opcion de mermelada, miel o maple ni pagando. Una opcion de jugo. Pero lo peor de todo fue encontrar un pedazo (grande) de cascara en el huevo. No cuidan detalles. A partir de eso no pudimos seguir comiendo en la posada, muy desagradable. Los almuerzos en la playa , una porcion minima de fruta. Un dia carne y un dia pollo son cosas que no provoca comer en la playa. El primer dia mandaron uma botella de coca cola y agua, el segundo no mandaron agua (excelente porq no hay forma de comprar en muchos de los cayos). La merienda unas arepas de anis mal presentadas babosas con el queso arriba como recalentadas. De verdad la comida super deficiente pero sobretodo sin cuidar NADA el aspecto y el detalle.
Las habitaciones no son feas, nos quedamos en el recuerdo by eva (solo dormimos ahi el resto se hace todo en la posada eva), en el lavamano no sale agua  practicamente, mientras que en la ducha si por lo que es obvio que no han arreglado ese problema porq no han querido, no es un tema de falta de agua en la isla porque sino la ducha no saldria agua tampoco,  el aire gotea y el ultimo dia nos conseguimos una cucaracha. Las toallas son minimas super desgastadas.
No iba a perder mi tiempo dejando un comentario , pero me parece importante que hayan comentarios mas sinceros porq cuando escogimos la posada nos guiamos por los comentarios y habian muchos positivos no entiendo como no hay quejas de todo los que nos paso a nosotros. No se si es que no pueden dar el mismo servicio cuando estan full (fuimos en plena semana santa) pero NO LA RECOMIENDO Y NO VUELVO!

Me mandaron a poner la rese√±a en el recuerdo entonces la pegar√© tambien en el recuerdo, ya que ahi es donde dormimos‚Ä¶

Creo que la idea de los comentarios negativos es aprender y corregir los errores que esten en sus manos, no buscar desacreditar y tratar de tapar errores que si existen! Porq de eso se tratan los servicios de mejorar gracias a comentarios como estos‚Ä¶

Probablemente, no arreglen nada de lo que dijimos y sigan diciendo que todo es culpa de cualquier otra cosa

review_text:
Top marks for the crew at Play! (the guys teaching kitesurfers and making sure that you're safe and enjoying your time there!)
Even though I didn't actually hired any of their equipment or services (I brought my own and kited independently), every day they helped me set up, launch, land and everything in between... that's a mark of great people!
They were constantly monitoring that all kiters were safe and that made me enjoy my sessions even more.
I'll recommend them to everyone I know and will be back!

The dedicated staff at Posada Sabbia, led by housekeepers Geraldine Novoa and Claudia Puccini, ensures that every corner of the inn is spotless and inviting, creating an atmosphere that complements the natural beauty of the surroundings. Butlers Gregory Romero and Ram√≥n Marcano serve with a keen eye for detail and a genuine desire to cater to every guest's whim, setting a new standard for personal service.

At the heart of the Posada Sabbia experience is the exceptional cuisine crafted by Chef Abraham Hernandez, with Sous Chef Leonardo Urbina providing essential support. Their culinary creations are a reflection of the island's bounty and the chefs' ingenuity. The dinner on March 12th was a journey through flavor, beginning with a refreshing white fish crudo, zesty with Nikkei sauce and ceviche-style vegetables, followed by a vibrant salad with creamy goat cheese and almonds, dressed in a perfectly balanced gastrique.

The mains were a testament to the kitchen's mastery of seafood and local flavors: octopus with a smoky paprika and wine sauce, accompanied by hearty rustic potatoes and the bright notes of chimichurri, and a perfectly executed tempura fish of the day, paired with a complex chaufa rice and a creamy cashew sauce.

Posada Sabbia's beach service is renowned as the best on the island, with attentive staff ensuring that guests' every need is met while they soak up the sun and enjoy the tranquil paradise that is Los Roques.

On March 13th, the culinary delights continued with starters like the crispy langoustines in a tangy passionfruit mayo, and the tender chicken with cooling tzatziki and a flavorful romesco emulsion. The mains featured a zesty linguini al Limoncello criollo with succulent shrimp and a perfectly grilled tenderloin, complemented by a smooth potato pur√©e and a luxurious mushroom wine sauce.

Posada Sabbia by LD, through its combination of exceptional dining, a meticulous and caring staff, and the most attentive beach service, offers an experience that truly captures the essence of Los Roques. Guests leave not only with memories of the archipelago's natural splendor but also with the taste of Chef Abraham's exquisite dishes lingering on their palate, the warmth of the staff's service in their hearts, and the desire to return to this slice of paradise at the earliest opportunity.

review_text: I've stayed at Laguna twice now. The first time with friends, and the second with my husband and children. Both times, I have been very pleased with the service provided and quality of the staff. The posada is clean and maintained to a high standard. We were greeted at the airport, our luggage was carried to and from the air/boat port each time we went out. I like that everything is included, so trips to the nearby beaches (fransiski and madriski), and a lot of delicious food. They provide thermos cups, cool box, beach towels and a speaker.

review_text:
Pueblo ubicado dentro del Parque Nacional Henri Pittier, Choron√≠ debe su urbanizaci√≥n al proceso de
dominio del territorio de los Valles de Aragua y de la regi√≥n costera. Conocido como Santa Clara de Choron√≠, este pueblo fue inicialmente una encomienda de L√°zaro V√°zquez y en 1602 pas√≥ a manos del capit√°n Diego deOvalle. A partir de 1619 fue erigido como Pueblo de Indios y en 1622 pas√≥ a ser Pueblo de Doctrina. En el a√±o 1772 ya se registran 53 casas en las que habitaban 44 familias de trabajadores de las haciendas circunvecinas. Choron√≠ es un centro urbano tradicional donde predomina la disposici√≥n de calles y manzanas en forma reticular. Las calles presentan leves pendientes por la accidentada topograf√≠a y la presencia de r√≠os que surcan el lugar. Las edificaciones en
su mayor√≠a son de una sola planta, con fachadas continuas y vanos rectangulares. En el centro del pueblo destaca la presencia de la Iglesia Santa Clara (patrona de Choron√≠). El √°rea del centro poblado fue declarada en 1979 Zona de Valor hist√≥rico-ambiental seg√∫n Gaceta Oficial N¬∞ 31.716. Se trata de un conjunto de 70 casas construidas
seg√∫n los c√°nones coloniales  en torno a la plaza Mayor. Siguiendo estos par√°metros las edificaciones que colindan con la plaza son las consideradas de mayor importancia comunal, como la iglesia, la prefectura, la junta parroquial, entre otras. Las v√≠as originalmente eran empedradas, pero actualmente son de concreto armado. El casco hist√≥rico de Choron√≠, en especial la calle Real que lo atraviesa, constituye un retazo de la historia colonial venezolana.

place_address: via, Parque Nacional Morrocoy, Agua Salobre 2055, Falc√≥n, Venezuela
review_text:
Nos trataron como VIPS!!!

They treated us like VIPS our first time there!!  We were looking for a last minute place to stay to go the the 'cayos' this weekend and we stumbled on to Las Canas - we're happy that we did.

It's a clean, comfortable place with a 3 nice pools to sit and relax, and a great little seating area too.  Dinner was tasty and breakfast was more than I could eat.

The room that we stayed in had a reasonable connection to the wifi, strong A/C and they had hot water, which is really nice to come back to after a day at the beach.

They also provided us with a 'to-go' lunch and a cooler for a reasonable fee.  Also, they provided us with transportation to and from the dock, and we were able to pay for our boat rides at the posada as well.

I'd highly recommend this posada to all my friends and I'm looking forward to visiting again.

place_address: Tucacas 2055, Falc√≥n, Venezuela
review_text:
I recently had the pleasure of staying at what I can confidently describe as the best posada in Tucacas. From the moment I arrived, I was greeted with warm hospitality and an atmosphere that truly made me feel at home. Allow me to share my thoughts on this wonderful experience.

First and foremost, the accommodations at this posada were exceptional. The rooms were not only clean and well-maintained but also beautifully decorated, giving them a cozy and inviting ambiance. I felt like I was staying in a home away from home, and the comfortable beds ensured a restful night's sleep after long days at the beach.

Speaking of the beach, the location of this posada was absolutely perfect. It was just a stone's throw away from the pristine shores of Tucacas, allowing for easy access to the breathtaking beaches. The environment was serene and tranquil, making it an ideal place to unwind and relax.

Now, let's talk about the food. The meals served at this posada were nothing short of delicious. Whether it was the hearty breakfasts to start the day or the flavorful seafood dishes for dinner, every bite was a culinary delight. The menu featured a variety of options to cater to different tastes, and I couldn't get enough of the fresh, local flavors.

What truly sets this posada apart, though, is the impeccable attention to detail and outstanding service provided by the staff. They went above and beyond to ensure that my stay was comfortable and enjoyable. Whether I needed assistance with booking activities, arranging transportation, or simply seeking recommendations, they were always eager to help.

One of the unique features of this posada that I absolutely loved was the inclusion of free pets. It was heartwarming to see well-behaved and friendly dogs and cats roaming around the property. They added an extra layer of charm to the place, and I couldn't resist petting and playing with them during my stay.

In conclusion, my experience at the best posada in Tucacas was nothing short of exceptional. From the excellent accommodations and delicious food to the warm and attentive staff and the delightful presence of free pets, every aspect of my stay was top-notch. If you're looking for a memorable beach getaway in Tucacas, I wholeheartedly recommend this posada for an unforgettable experience.
